      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant, delivering linear torque via Variocam Plus technology. Mated to a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle, the drivetrain remains tight with crisp shift gates. The chassis benefits from a multi-link rear suspension setup, providing that signature rear-engine pendulum effect with excellent mechanical grip. Recent preventative maintenance includes an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal, ensuring the integrity of the intermediate shaft. The hydraulic steering rack offers communicative feedback, and the four-piston Monobloc calipers provide consistent, fade-free deceleration. While the finish shows light patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the engine pulls strongly to redline with a clean oil analysis history.",
